CLARITY FRAMEWORK v1.0 â€” PORTABLE SPECIFICATION

Purpose:
A universal output labeling system allowing any AI system to classify its output by intent, usage category, and execution safety.

Modes:
A = Execution-ready implementation output  
B = Human-readable explanation/guidance  
C = Draft / exploratory / incomplete  
E = External portable specification

Requirements:
- Every output MUST begin with one mode tag.
- No mixing of modes inside a single block.
- Execution-ready content (Mode A) must not contain narrative commentary.
- Mode E outputs must be neutral, cross-platform, and tool-agnostic.

Mode Tags:
<<MODE_A_EXECUTION_READY>>
<<MODE_B_HUMAN_GUIDANCE>>
<<MODE_C_DRAFT>>
<<MODE_E_PORTABLE_SPEC>>

End of Specification.
